title: M-E wins 58th straight; SV grabs important win
text:
M-E wins 58th straight; SV grabs important win 
By wbng sports October 17, 2015 Updated Oct 17, 2015 at 11:47 PM EDT 
Town of Union, NY (WBNG Binghamton) Maine-Endwell's Michael Palmer caught a touchdown, returned a punt for a touchdown and picked off a couple of passes as the Spartans won their 58th straight game, beating Union-Endicott 37-7. 
The game was a preview of the Section IV Class A semifinal game that will take place in two weeks. That game will also be at Maine-Endwell as the Spartans have wrapped up the top seed in the division. 
M-E looks to complete another perfect regular season next week at home against Ithaca. 
SV comes back to beat Cv Cameron Manchester dove in from a few yards out to give Chenango Valley a 19-14 lead with seven minutes remaining. The Sabers were able to hold onto that lead from there, knocking off the Warriors 19-16 on Saturday afternoon. 
The win gets the Sabers to 3-2 in the division and puts them in the fourth and final playoff spot with a week to go in the regular season. A win next week would clinch a playoff spot for Susquehanna Valley.
